cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CL 

This paper is primarily focused on visual recognition and the limitations of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) in learning visual relations. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of machine learning algorithms, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the limitations of CNNs, which suggests that it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the use of attention and perceptual grouping, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language).
